history.content: Math 136 is probably the closest to cs172

I read on the Computer Science Facebook page that CS 172 is not going to be offered next year. Someone mentioned that faculty members aren't too interested in teaching it.

Since that's the case, is there any course that covers similar, or more advanced material, than CS 172? A graduate course perhaps? I especially want to learn computability in more depth: I have no idea what a Turing machine is, for example.

I'm willing to read some / all of Sipser's book to prepare myself for a more advanced class. I am asking now so I can plan out my summer reading schedule to get a head start on that goal.

Thank you!
